content: Did not like this app at all. The information was very confusing and the articles are the same each week.

An awful app. No helpful tips. not interactive, not uplifting,not positive. The first line is a line that never leaves saying the below always check with you gp. Apart from one line of a tip there's nothing else changed week on week. I use a single pregnancy app that's so much better and free. This app isn't worth a penny!!!
Definitely not worth paying for as you can get better information from a quick Google search!

Just not at all worth paying for it. It has nothing just few articles taken from here and there sites. They don't even bother updating it with new ones. All they want is that one keeps posting pics. No new information not even weekly. Highly not recommended. What are you guys charging for?

Repeats the same info week to week. It only changes slightly to say weight 
and size of babies. It never gives any new articles so you read them all 
and your done. Total waste of money. The free apps give more info.

This app was nothing special. Definitely not worth paying for.  It never automatically alerted me to my weeks changing and only popped up after I went in.  It didn't have anything that my free apps didn't have. In fact, most articles just transferred me to babycenter, which is free.

Its ok, once i read all the articles theres is anymore to read. I like the name list i can creation. The weekly info is not much, very short. I get alot more information from Other free apps. And there doesnt seem to be much update to the app. This seems to be the best that it will get.
Didn't like it. It isn't worth the money
replyContent: Thank you for taking the time to review the app. Sorry to hear that you feel that way. I am always working on improving the app so if you have a time to give me more details, I would appropriate it. please contact me at help@twinpregnancyapp.com.

content: Why did I pay money for the same info I could get from other free pregnancy apps and a bunch of links to free websites. Not worth it.

content: I like how the size is accurate but I can't stand how summarized the weekly developments are or the what to expect. I like more details which is why I have another app to tell me details and keep track of everything.
replyContent: Hi Krystina, thank you for taking the time to review. We appreciate the feedback and will work on adding more details to the app in the future. With twins in your future you already need two of everything, we will try to make it so you don't need two apps. ;-)

content: Great app overall but I love all the links to recommended reading!

content: The free apps will tell you the same information, if not more.
replyContent: I'm sorry to hear you feel that way. I've tried to build an app that will benefit soon to be parents of twins. If you are not fully satisfied you can request a refund. If you need assistance doing so or have any requests you can reach me at help@twinpregnancyapp.com. Happy holidays!

content: I really like the way the app tells you things to look out for every week.  It is fun to imagine the size of the babies and fun to picture them the size of a passion fruit or melon.  The sources for  information are also very helpful.  Thanks for a great app.  Well worth the money!!
replyContent: Thanks for the great review! I'm glad you like the app. Please let me know if you have any feature requests or comments by emailing help@twinpregnancyapp.com.

content: This app is great! My family has a history of twins so this is just what I was a looking for! It has all the features I had hoped for and some that I hadn't expected. It's a great place to start learning about what to expect every step of the way through such an exciting and crazy stage of life. It also lets you save/manage your pictures and the names you are considering. The app runs smoothly, looks great!
replyContent: Thanks for the great review! I'm glad you like the app. Please let me know if you have any feature requests or comments by emailing help@twinpregnancyapp.com.

content: Love that it has weekly updates about your twin pregnancy, and the ability to share your progress on Facebook. Highly recommend to other twin moms.
replyContent: Thanks for the great review! I'm glad you like the app. Please let me know if you have any feature requests or comments by emailing help@twinpregnancyapp.com.

content: Crashes continuously when I try to upload pictures. When you pay for an app you should get what you pay for. Please fix! I tried again and it did the same thing, I sent a crash report this time. I hope y'all get it fixed soon. Thank you!
replyContent: I wanted to check back with you since the update. Are you still experiencing this issue? Hopefully now you can enjoy the app to its full potential. Happy holidays!

content: After trying several apps (Ovia, baby center, and the bump), it was very refreshing to download an app specifically made for parents expecting twins. The app has pertinent information and weekly updates that let you know what your beans are up to, their size, and symptoms you may experience.  There's nice features which include the ability to upload photos, make a list of baby names, read articles geared toward parents of multiples, and a countdown of days left. I highly recommend this app!
replyContent: Thanks for the great review! I'm glad you like the app. Please let me know if you have any feature requests or comments by emailing help@twinpregnancyapp.com.
